                <h1>The Birth of McDonald's: A Fast Food Revolution</h1>
                <p>The first McDonald's was opened in 1940 by brothers Richard and Maurice McDonald in San Bernardino, California. This fast-food pioneer introduced the "Speedee Service System," revolutionizing fast food concepts with a focus on efficiency and consistent quality. The success laid the groundwork for the global franchise we know today.</p>
